node.text:
The violent center of the Carina Nebula, a 460 light year wide monster holding some of the most beautiful gas and dust structures in the Milky Way for our eyes to see! 🔭

Follow @Spacespot to explore the Universe 🚀
⠀
At the center, the Mystic Mountain region is three light years in height and contains nascent stars which fire off jets of gas which can be seen streaming from the mountain peaks. The gas pillar is being slowly eroded by the light of the enormously large, massive young stars located above the pillar. ✨

node.text:
The Sturgeon Full Moon 🌕 (Composition with Jupiter and Saturn) 🪐

Why is it called that? Well, August’s full Moon is traditionally named Sturgeon Moon because the giant sturgeon, a species of giant bony fish, are readily caught during this part of the summer in North America’s Great Lakes.

Jupiter and Saturn are added to the image as the planets were in semi conjunction. Actual distance is larger than the image. Planets are scaled to be larger than the actual.
